texts.text: *Panting*
Impressive, Demon Tamer.

I commend your survival so far.
But I must bring it to an end.
*Bellows*
*Gulps*
Devil Download!
*Growls*
*Grunts*

We finally caught up with you,
Hikaru!
You... You were Dx2?

Yes, and very powerful Dx2
at that!
Wait a sec, Chi You!

We gotta send this guy safely
back home.
Let's talk it out, okay?
*Roars*

*Tsks* Something's wrong. He's
totally different from before.
Negotiation's not working.

Oh, well. Protecting human life
is more important now.

*Yells*
Bring it on!
*Growls*

>The Liberators' attack causes
the demon to begin to disappear.
*Groans*

Demon Tamer, as you hunt my kind
to extinction...

Do you think a better world
lies ahead?

You think a world without pain
or fighting exists?
(A what?)
I do! There has to be!
Fool.
Your dream is a joke.

You'll see. Your ignorance, the
insignificance of your dream...
>The demon disappears.

>The Liberators run up to Hikaru,
who stands completely still.
Hey, you okay, man?

You're going too hard, man. No
one could face all that alone.
Right.
Thanks. You saved me.

So, you're Dx2 from Tokyo?
I feel like we've met before.

I'm Megakin the MegaTuber.
I'm the branch leader and stuff.

Gotcha. Sorry my sister got
your people involved in this.

She's always been like that, as
you probably guessed.
Stubborn. Rash.

*Laughs* Twins. Y'all are
like peas in a pod.
So.

Why act alone without telling
anyone, even your twin?

Chi You seemed to have some
notes on your, uh, dream.
Erm, my dream. Right.
I'm just sick of this.
You mean being a Dx2?
No.

The endless fighting with
demons. It never stops.

I'm sick of people getting
caught in the crossfire.

We defeat demons one day, and
more appear the next.
It's always the same thing.

But for the people who die,
there's no "next day."
I mean, isn't that just bull?
If there weren't any demons...

Then things would be fine and
no one would have to die.

I can't disagree with any of
that, but...
That's why!

It's better for humanity if
a new God rules the world.
The world we have, its systems,

we leave them behind and start
fresh with another God's ethos.
Everything would be different!
Whoa, man, tap the brakes.

All due respect, but as branch
leader, I gotta nope out.

We can't trust demons with the
fate of humanity.

I, for one, believe humans gotta
work together for our future.

I wish it was that easy. But we
have to be realistic!

Then tell me, is there a god who
can create this "new world"?

There is! Mithras, the one who
created this Aura Gate!
Mithras?

He's a sun god who used to fight
against the current God.
But he's been totally forgotten.

I heard about him at this Aura
Gate, and it all made sense.

If such a powerful god came back
and controlled things...

We could change this cycle
of pointless sacrifice.

So, your dream is to change the
world, then?
Yeah, exactly!

Mithras feels bad for us having
to live in this world!

Too many innocent people are
dying.

And it'll never change as long
as the current God allows it.

Mithras says he wouldn't sit on
his hands. If he had the power,

he would turn into the new God
and save us all!

That would be uplifting, if it
were true.
Emphasis on the "if."

But it is true! He once held his
own, as a god!

I think I understand what's
going on here now.

Hikaru's slaughtering demons to
give Mithras their strength.

That's why he keeps fighting
demons on his own.
Exactly! It's a ritual.

I'm actually reenacting an old
ritual.

It'll help bring Mithras back to
full strength faster.

They used to call him "Mithras
the Bull Slayer!"
*Laughs*

I'll stop the needless killing!
No more civilian casualties!

I don't care who gets in my way.
I'm doing this. I won't stop.

This isn't good. He's totally
obsessed.

He's not the type to ignore
advice from others.
Brainwashed by Mithras, maybe?
I dunno.

Either way, he's in no place to
make rational decisions.

Something inside him might have
just snapped.

Death is, after all, a wound
that runs deep.

>Impassioned, Hikaru draws
closer to the three of them.

If you help me, we can do this
even faster!
Come on, join me!
Don't you hate it, too?

All these people dying just
because of demons?
Of course, we hate it.

But what makes you trust Mithras
so much?

Why would everything be so much
better under him?

How much do you actually know
about him, anyway?
Ugh! Come on, I...
Oh, my.

Non-believers seem to have
sneaked into the ritual space.
That voice...
Mithras!

Huh. What a well-timed
appearance.
Hmph, no matter.

It was surely fate that brought
you here.

I grant salvation to all who
seek it.

Now then, Hikaru.
You have served me well.

I can feel the power from your
efforts flowing into me.

It's nearly as it was when I
reigned as the one true God.

Yes, Mithras! The time of your
revival is almost here!
Indeed.

And now, just one last step
remains.

It is time for the next ritual.
Let us begin.
Bring me my power!

Run red, blood of most holy
sacrifice! Flow, life force!

>Summoned by Mithras, demons
appear before the Liberators.
*Roars*
Vengeance for our kin!
We're surrounded!

My faithful! In my name,
defeat these creatures!
And grant me more power!

Power as I once knew, power for
my glorious revival!
